# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>                         ← this line, ≤72 chars
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TYPE (pick one):
#   feat     · new user-visible feature
#   fix      · bug fix
#   docs     · documentation only
#   refactor · restructure, no behaviour change
#   test     · tests only
#   chore    · tooling, deps, config
#   perf     · performance improvement
#   ci       · CI/CD pipeline
#   revert   · reverts a previous commit
#   style    · whitespace / lint only
#
# SCOPE (pick the one that owns the change):
#   Apps   → api | consumer | merchant | courier | wholesale | backoffice | website
#   Pkgs   → domain | data | core-auth | core-network | ui-kit | utils
#   Other  → infra | docs | workspace
#
# SUBJECT RULES:
#   · Imperative mood  →  "Add X"  not  "Added X"
#   · ≤ 72 chars total (type + scope + subject)
#   · Lowercase after the colon
#   · No trailing period
#   · No ticket numbers here — use footers below
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# [leave one blank line, then write the BODY if needed]
#
# Explain WHY — the diff already shows WHAT.
# Wrap at 72 chars. Include migration steps if any.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# [leave one blank line, then add FOOTERS if applicable]
#
# Implements: REQ-XX-NNN        ← PRD requirement this satisfies
# See: ADR-NNN                  ← architecture decision referenced
# Refs: #NNN                    ← related GitHub issue (not closing)
# Closes: #NNN                  ← GitHub issue resolved by this commit
# BREAKING CHANGE: <desc>       ← public contract change (describe migration)
# Co-authored-by: Name <email>
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Full convention: docs/COMMIT_CONVENTION.md
# Lines starting with # are stripped from the commit message.
